        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Evaluation with Cardiovascular MR Imaging of Baffles and Conduits Used in Palliation or Repair of Congenital Heart Disease" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jimmy C.  Lu" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Adam L.  Dorfman" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Anil K.  Attili" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Maryam  Ghadimi Mahani" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jonathan R.  Dillman" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Prachi P.  Agarwal" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Various baffles and conduits used in repair and palliation of congenital heart disease are reviewed, and an approach to their evaluation with cardiovascular MR imaging is discussed." /><meta name="Description" content="Various baffles and conduits used in repair and palliation of congenital heart disease are reviewed, and an approach to their evaluation with cardiovascular MR imaging is discussed." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="A wide array of baffles and conduits are used in repair or palliation of congenital heart disease, which is the most common major birth defect, often with complex redirection of blood flow to achie..." /><meta name="Description" content="A wide array of baffles and conduits are used in repair or palliation of congenital heart disease, which is the most common major birth defect, often with complex redirection of blood flow to achie..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2012-05-05" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="publisher-id" content="115096" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.323115096" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.323115096" /><meta name="dc.Lan